    "body": "## Summary\n- fix an SM90 FMHA V2 dispatch hash collision between `attention_mask_type` and `enable_skip_softmax`\n- restore the correct full-mask skip-softmax kernel selection instead of relying on a Python-side guard\n- add an SM90 regression test that exercises full-mask prefill with skip-softmax and verifies threshold forwarding\n\n## Root cause\n`ContextAttentionMaskType::CUSTOM_MASK` needs 3 bits in the FMHA V2 hash. The previous packing overlapped the mask-type field with the skip-softmax bit, so `PADDING + skip-softmax` collided with `CUSTOM_MASK + no skip-softmax` and dispatched the wrong kernel on SM90.\n\n## Validation\n- `pytest -q tests/unittest/_torch/attention/test_skip_softmax_sm90.py`\n- `python work/20260416/repro_skip_softmax_sm90.py --mask full --skip-softmax --disable-sm90-full-mask-guard`\n- `compute-sanitizer --tool memcheck --target-processes all python work/20260416/repro_skip_softmax_sm90.py --mask full --skip-softmax --disable-sm90-full-mask-guard`\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Improved internal code maintainability in attention kernel implementation through named constants and validation checks.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added SM90-specific unit tests to validate skip-softmax attention configuration and behavior.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
